/*The method of computing the yearly depreciation of the value of an item is given by the
following equation:
ğ·ğ‘’ğ‘ğ‘Ÿğ‘’ğ‘ğ‘–ğ‘ğ‘¡ğ‘–ğ‘œğ‘› =(ğ‘ƒğ‘¢ğ‘Ÿğ‘â„ğ‘ğ‘ ğ‘’ ğ‘ƒğ‘Ÿğ‘–ğ‘ğ‘’ âˆ’ ğ‘†ğ‘ğ‘™ğ‘£ğ‘ğ‘”ğ‘’ ğ‘‰ğ‘ğ‘™ğ‘¢ğ‘’)/ğ‘Œğ‘’ğ‘ğ‘Ÿğ‘  ğ‘œğ‘“ ğ‘†ğ‘’ğ‘Ÿğ‘£ğ‘–ğ‘ğ‘’
Write a program to determine the salvage value of an item when the purchase price, years
of service and the annual depreciation are given by the user. */

#include <stdio.h>
int main()
{
	float purchase,yos,salv,dep;
	printf("Enter Purchase Price, Annual depreciation amount, and Years of service \n");
	scanf("%f%f%f",&purchase,&dep,&yos);
	salv=purchase - (dep*yos);
	printf("Salvage value is %f",salv);
	return 0;
}

	
